| style="color:#000; padding:2px 5px 5px;" | <div id="mp-dyk">
''From Wikipedia's [[Wikipedia:Recent additions|new and recently improved content]]:''
<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.5em;">
[[File:Vera Bogdanovskaia.png|100x100px|Vera Bogdanovskaia]]
</div>
* ... that '''[[Vera Bogdanovskaia]]''' ''(pictured)'' was killed in 1896 while trying to make [[Methylidynephosphane|H-C≡P]], a chemical not successfully synthesized until 1961? 
* ... that after the British [[National Board for Prices and Incomes]] was closed, member '''[[Hugh Clegg (industrial relations)|Hugh Clegg]]''' wrote a book entitled ''How to Run an [[Incomes Policy]], and Why We Made Such a Mess of the Last One''?
* ... that '''[[Pete Hampton]]''' is believed to be the first [[African American]] to make a [[harmonica]] recording?
* ... that electronic musician [[Peaches (musician)|Peaches]] is featured on the remix of [[Natalia Kills]]' song "'''[[Trouble (Natalia Kills song)|Trouble]]'''"?
* ... that '''[[Qingdao Airlines]]''', a Chinese air carrier that launched operations in April 2014, aims to become a "boutique airline"?
* ... that football coach '''[[Choo Seng Quee]]''' was a British agent during [[World War&nbsp;II]]?
